#. <section class="sutta" id="sn42.9"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn42.9:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 42"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 42"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn42.9:0.2"
msgid "1. Gāmaṇivagga"
msgstr "1. Chiefs"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn42.9:0.3"
msgid "9. Kulasutta"
msgstr "9. Families"

# Umm, Nalanda is in Magadha?
#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi4.323"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn42.9:1.1"
msgid ""
"Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā kosalesu cārikaṃ caramāno mahatā bhikkhusaṅghena "
"saddhiṃ yena nāḷandā tadavasari."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was wandering in the land of the Kosalans together "
"with a large Saṅgha of mendicants when he arrived at Nāḷandā."

msgctxt "sn42.9:1.2"
msgid "Tatra sudaṃ bhagavā nāḷandāyaṃ viharati pāvārikambavane."
msgstr "There he stayed near Nālandā in Pāvārika’s mango grove."

# See BB’s note.
#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn42.9:2.1"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena nāḷandā dubbhikkhā hoti dvīhitikā setaṭṭhikā "
"salākāvuttā."
msgstr ""
"Now that was a time of famine and scarcity in Nāḷandā, with blighted crops "
"turned to straw."

msgctxt "sn42.9:2.2"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena nigaṇṭho nāṭaputto nāḷandāyaṃ paṭivasati mahatiyā "
"nigaṇṭhaparisāya saddhiṃ."
msgstr ""
"At that time Nigaṇṭha Nāṭaputta was residing at Nāḷandā together with a "
"large assembly of Jain ascetics."

msgctxt "sn42.9:2.3"
msgid ""
"Atha kho asibandhakaputto gāmaṇi nigaṇṭhasāvako yena nigaṇṭho nāṭaputto "
"tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā nigaṇṭhaṃ nāṭaputtaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ "
"nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho asibandhakaputtaṃ gāmaṇiṃ nigaṇṭho nāṭaputto "
"etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"Then Asibandhaka’s son the chief, who was a disciple of the Jains, went up "
"to Nigaṇṭha Nāṭaputta, bowed, and sat down to one side. Nigaṇṭha Nāṭaputta "
"said to him:"

msgctxt "sn42.9:2.4"
msgid "“ehi tvaṃ, gāmaṇi, samaṇassa gotamassa vādaṃ āropehi."
msgstr "“Come, chief, refute the ascetic Gotama’s doctrine."

msgctxt "sn42.9:2.5"
msgid "Evaṃ te kalyāṇo kittisaddo abbhuggacchissati:"
msgstr "Then you will get a good reputation:"

msgctxt "sn42.9:2.6"
msgid ""
"‘asibandhakaputtena gāmaṇinā samaṇassa gotamassa evaṃmahiddhikassa "
"evaṃmahānubhāvassa vādo āropito’”ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Asibandhaka’s son the chief refuted the doctrine of the ascetic Gotama, so "
"mighty and powerful!’\""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi4.324"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn42.9:3.1"
msgid ""
"“Kathaṃ panāhaṃ, bhante, samaṇassa gotamassa evaṃmahiddhikassa "
"evaṃmahānubhāvassa vādaṃ āropessāmī”ti?"
msgstr "“But sir, how am I to do this?”"

msgctxt "sn42.9:3.2"
msgid ""
"“Ehi tvaṃ, gāmaṇi, yena samaṇo gotamo tenupasaṅkama; upasaṅkamitvā samaṇaṃ "
"gotamaṃ evaṃ vadehi:"
msgstr "“Here, brahmin, go to the ascetic Gotama and say to him:"

#. VAR: anuddayaṃ → anudayaṃ (s1-3, km, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "sn42.9:3.3"
msgid ""
"‘nanu, bhante, bhagavā anekapariyāyena kulānaṃ anuddayaṃ vaṇṇeti, anurakkhaṃ "
"vaṇṇeti, anukampaṃ vaṇṇetī’ti?"
msgstr ""
"‘Sir, don’t you in many ways praise kindness, protection, and compassion for "
"families?’"

msgctxt "sn42.9:3.4"
msgid "Sace kho, gāmaṇi, samaṇo gotamo evaṃ puṭṭho evaṃ byākaroti:"
msgstr "When he’s asked this, if he answers:"

msgctxt "sn42.9:3.5"
msgid ""
"‘evaṃ, gāmaṇi, tathāgato anekapariyāyena kulānaṃ anuddayaṃ vaṇṇeti, "
"anurakkhaṃ vaṇṇeti, anukampaṃ vaṇṇetī’ti, tamenaṃ tvaṃ evaṃ vadeyyāsi:"
msgstr "‘Indeed I do, chief,’ say this to him:"

# Note the similarity to Mahakassapa’s criticism of Ananda at SN 16.11
msgctxt "sn42.9:3.6"
msgid ""
"‘atha kiñcarahi, bhante, bhagavā dubbhikkhe dvīhitike setaṭṭhike salākāvutte "
"mahatā bhikkhusaṃghena saddhiṃ cārikaṃ carati?"
msgstr ""
"‘So what exactly are you doing, wandering together with this large Saṅgha of "
"mendicants during a time of famine and scarcity, with blighted crops turned "
"to straw?"

msgctxt "sn42.9:3.7"
msgid ""
"Ucchedāya bhagavā kulānaṃ paṭipanno, anayāya bhagavā kulānaṃ paṭipanno, "
"upaghātāya bhagavā kulānaṃ paṭipanno’ti."
msgstr "The Buddha is practicing to annihilate, collapse, and ruin families!’"

#. VAR: sakkhati → sakkhiti (bj)
msgctxt "sn42.9:3.8"
msgid ""
"Imaṃ kho te, gāmaṇi, samaṇo gotamo ubhatokoṭikaṃ pañhaṃ puṭṭho neva sakkhati "
"uggilituṃ, neva sakkhati ogilitun”ti."
msgstr ""
"When you put this dilemma to him, the Buddha won’t be able to either spit it "
"out or swallow it down.”"

msgctxt "sn42.9:3.9"
msgid ""
"“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho asibandhakaputto gāmaṇi nigaṇṭhassa nāṭaputtassa "
"paṭissutvā uṭṭhāyāsanā nigaṇṭhaṃ nāṭaputtaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā "
"yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ "
"nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho asibandhakaputto gāmaṇi bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"“Yes, sir,” replied Asibandhaka’s son. He got up from his seat, bowed, and "
"respectfully circled Nigaṇṭha Nāṭaputta, keeping him on his right. Then he "
"went to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and said to him:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi4.325"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn42.9:4.1"
msgid ""
"“Nanu, bhante, bhagavā anekapariyāyena kulānaṃ anuddayaṃ vaṇṇeti, anurakkhaṃ "
"vaṇṇeti, anukampaṃ vaṇṇetī”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“Sir, don’t you in many ways praise kindness, protection, and compassion for "
"families?”"

msgctxt "sn42.9:4.2"
msgid ""
"“Evaṃ, gāmaṇi, tathāgato anekapariyāyena kulānaṃ anuddayaṃ vaṇṇeti, "
"anurakkhaṃ vaṇṇeti, anukampaṃ vaṇṇetī”ti."
msgstr "“Indeed I do, chief.”"

msgctxt "sn42.9:4.3"
msgid ""
"“Atha kiñcarahi, bhante, bhagavā dubbhikkhe dvīhitike setaṭṭhike salākāvutte "
"mahatā bhikkhusaṃghena saddhiṃ cārikaṃ carati?"
msgstr ""
"“So what exactly are you doing, wandering together with this large Saṅgha of "
"mendicants during a time of famine and scarcity, with blighted crops turned "
"to straw?"

msgctxt "sn42.9:4.4"
msgid ""
"Ucchedāya bhagavā kulānaṃ paṭipanno, anayāya bhagavā kulānaṃ paṭipanno, "
"upaghātāya bhagavā kulānaṃ paṭipanno”ti."
msgstr "The Buddha is practicing to annihilate, collapse, and ruin families!”"

#. VAR: ekanavutikappe → ekanavuto kappo (bj, s1-3, km) | ekanavutikappo (pts1)
msgctxt "sn42.9:4.5"
msgid ""
"“Ito so, gāmaṇi, ekanavutikappe yamahaṃ anussarāmi, nābhijānāmi kiñci kulaṃ "
"pakkabhikkhānuppadānamattena upahatapubbaṃ."
msgstr ""
"“Well, chief, I recollect ninety eons back but I’m not aware of any family "
"that’s been ruined merely by offering some cooked alms-food."

msgctxt "sn42.9:4.6"
msgid ""
"Atha kho yāni tāni kulāni aḍḍhāni mahaddhanāni mahābhogāni "
"pahūtajātarūparajatāni pahūtavittūpakaraṇāni pahūtadhanadhaññāni, sabbāni "
"tāni dānasambhūtāni ceva saccasambhūtāni ca sāmaññasambhūtāni ca."
msgstr ""
"Rather, rich, affluent, and wealthy families—with lots of gold and silver, "
"lots of property and assets, and lots of money and grain—all acquired their "
"wealth because of generosity, truth, and restraint."

msgctxt "sn42.9:4.7"
msgid "Aṭṭha kho, gāmaṇi, hetū, aṭṭha paccayā kulānaṃ upaghātāya."
msgstr "Chief, there are eight causes and conditions for the ruin of families."

#. VAR: nihitaṃ vā ṭhānā vigacchati → nihitaṃ vā nādhigacchanti (bj, pts1)
#. VAR: kule vā kulaṅgāroti → kulānaṃ vā kulaṅgāro (bj) | kule va kulaṅgāroti (pts1)
msgctxt "sn42.9:4.8"
msgid ""
"Rājato vā kulāni upaghātaṃ gacchanti, corato vā kulāni upaghātaṃ gacchanti, "
"aggito vā kulāni upaghātaṃ gacchanti, udakato vā kulāni upaghātaṃ gacchanti, "
"nihitaṃ vā ṭhānā vigacchati, duppayuttā vā kammantā vipajjanti, kule vā "
"kulaṅgāroti uppajjati, yo te bhoge vikirati vidhamati viddhaṃseti, "
"aniccatāyeva aṭṭhamīti."
msgstr ""
"Their ruin stems from rulers, bandits, fire, or flood. Or their savings "
"vanish. Or their business fails due to not applying themselves to work. Or a "
"wastrel is born into the family who squanders and fritters away their "
"wealth. And impermanence is the eighth."

msgctxt "sn42.9:4.9"
msgid "Ime kho, gāmaṇi, aṭṭha hetū, aṭṭha paccayā kulānaṃ upaghātāya."
msgstr "These are the eight causes and conditions for the ruin of families."

msgctxt "sn42.9:4.10"
msgid ""
"Imesu kho, gāmaṇi, aṭṭhasu hetūsu, aṭṭhasu paccayesu saṃvijjamānesu yo maṃ "
"evaṃ vadeyya:"
msgstr "Given that these eight reasons are found, suppose someone says this:"

msgctxt "sn42.9:4.11"
msgid ""
"‘ucchedāya bhagavā kulānaṃ paṭipanno, anayāya bhagavā kulānaṃ paṭipanno, "
"upaghātāya bhagavā kulānaṃ paṭipanno’ti, "
msgstr "‘The Buddha is practicing to annihilate, collapse, and ruin families!’ "

msgctxt "sn42.9:4.12"
msgid ""
"taṃ, gāmaṇi, vācaṃ appahāya taṃ cittaṃ appahāya taṃ diṭṭhiṃ "
"appaṭinissajjitvā yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ niraye”ti."
msgstr ""
"Unless they give up that speech and thought, and let go of that view, they "
"will be cast down to hell.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn42.9:5.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, asibandhakaputto gāmaṇi bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "When he said this, Asibandhaka’s son the chief said to the Buddha:"

msgctxt "sn42.9:5.2"
msgid "“abhikkantaṃ, bhante, abhikkantaṃ, bhante … pe …"
msgstr "“Excellent, sir! Excellent! …"

msgctxt "sn42.9:5.3"
msgid "upāsakaṃ maṃ bhagavā dhāretu ajjatagge pāṇupetaṃ saraṇaṃ gatan”ti."
msgstr ""
"From this day forth, may the Buddha remember me as a lay follower who has "
"gone for refuge for life.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn42.9:5.4"
msgid "Navamaṃ."
msgstr ""
